    {"repo": "sg-evals/rust--01f6ddf7", "path": "compiler/rustc_proc_macro/Cargo.toml"},
    {"repo": "sg-evals/rust--01f6ddf7", "path": "library/proc_macro/src/lib.rs"},
    {"repo": "sg-evals/rust--01f6ddf7", "path": "library/proc_macro/src/bridge/mod.rs"},
    {"repo": "sg-evals/rust--01f6ddf7", "path": "library/proc_macro/src/bridge/server.rs"},
    {"repo": "sg-evals/rust--01f6ddf7", "path": "library/proc_macro/src/bridge/client.rs"}
  ],
  "symbols": [
    {"repo": "sg-evals/rust--01f6ddf7", "path": "library/proc_macro/src/bridge/mod.rs", "symbol": "BridgeConfig"},
    {"repo": "sg-evals/rust--01f6ddf7", "path": "library/proc_macro/src/bridge/server.rs", "symbol": "ExecutionStrategy"}
  ],
  "text": "1. SERVO STYLE/SELECTORS CRATES: In sg-evals/servo--be6a2f99, the `style` and `selectors` crates no longer live under `components/style/` or `components/selectors/`. They have been extracted to an external repository (https://github.com/servo/stylo). The root workspace `Cargo.toml` (Cargo.toml) declares them as git workspace dependencies: `selectors = { git = \"https://github.com/servo/stylo\", rev = \"3b46f3ef27eb14ca276b4bf3ff041a6c43d93827\" }` and `stylo = { git = \"https://github.com/servo/stylo\", rev = \"3b46f3ef27eb14ca276b4bf3ff041a6c43d93827\" }` (the `style` crate is published as `stylo`). The patch comment section of the workspace Cargo.toml documents that `selectors` lives at `../stylo/selectors` and `stylo` (style) at `../stylo/style` in the stylo repo. Additional stylo-family crates declared in the workspace include: `servo_arc`, `stylo_atoms`, `stylo_config`, `stylo_dom`, `stylo_malloc_size_of`, `stylo_traits`, all from the same git rev. Components like `tests/unit/style/Cargo.toml` (crate name `style_tests`) depend on `selectors`, `stylo`, `stylo_atoms`, `stylo_traits`, `servo_arc`, `cssparser`, etc.\n\n2. SERVO STYLE ENTRY POINT: `components/style/lib.rs` does not exist in sg-evals/servo--be6a2f99 because the style system has been moved to the external servo/stylo repository. The workspace Cargo.toml comment shows the mapping: `stylo = { path = \"../stylo/style\" }`, so the main entry point would be `style/src/lib.rs` in the stylo repo.\n\n3. RUST-LANG/RUST SELECTORS DEPENDENCY: No crate under `compiler/` or `library/` in sg-evals/rust--01f6ddf7 depends on Servo's `selectors` crate. The Rust compiler does not share the CSS selector crate with Servo.\n\n4. PROC_MACRO BRIDGE: The proc_macro bridge in rust-lang/rust is defined in `library/proc_macro/src/bridge/mod.rs` (key type: `BridgeConfig`, the C-repr struct configuring the server-client connection) and `library/proc_macro/src/bridge/server.rs` (key trait: `ExecutionStrategy` with `run_bridge_and_client`). The `compiler/rustc_proc_macro/Cargo.toml` crate provides a wrapper that points its `[lib] path` to `../../library/proc_macro/src/lib.rs`, making the same proc_macro library available to the compiler. The bridge modules include: `mod.rs` (core types/RPC protocol), `client.rs` (client-side Bridge TLS), `server.rs` (ExecutionStrategy, SameThread), `rpc.rs`, `handle.rs`, `buffer.rs`, `arena.rs`, `symbol.rs`, `fxhash.rs`, `closure.rs`, `selfless_reify.rs`."
}

